Concepts
-Meant to decouple abstraction and implementation
-Encapsulation, Composition, Inheritance
-Changes in abstraction won't effect the client
-Changes in abstraction won't affect client
-Details won't be right

Examples
    JDBC Drivers

Design
-uses interfaces and abstract classes
-More than composition
-Expect change from bothe sides
-abstraction, implementor, refined abstraction, concrete implementor

Derek Banas explains it better:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9jIgSsIfh_8
-Two layers of abstraction between a concrete, where one abstract class is dependent on another